==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*badjan'' ‘dug sleeping-place’, from Indo-European ''*bhedh-'' ‘dig’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[bed]], Old Saxon [[bed]] (Dutch [[bed#Dutch|bed]]), Old High German [[betti]] (German [[Bett]]), Old Norse [[beðr]], Gothic [[𐌱𐌰𐌳𐌹]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[βοθυρος]] ‘pit’, Latin [[fossa]] ‘ditch’, Baltic ''*bed-'' (Latvian [[bedre]] ‘hole’), Celtic ''*bed-'' (Welsh [[bedd#Welsh|bedd]], Breton [[bez]] ‘grave’); and probably of Russian [[бодать]].

